00:43.042 --> 00:44.753
THAT WAS A HOOT!

01:06.149 --> 01:08.026
(<i> sighing</i> )

01:11.237 --> 01:13.615
GAA!

01:13.698 --> 01:16.451
(<i> fly buzzing</i> )

01:17.744 --> 01:21.164
{\an1}Bug:
HELP. HELP.

01:21.247 --> 01:23.291
{\an1}GET US OUT OF HERE.
WE'RE DYING.

01:24.918 --> 01:29.798
Rocko:
IT IS TIME TO MOP.

01:31.716 --> 01:34.636
(<i> grunting</i> )

01:35.762 --> 01:38.348
(<i> crunching</i> )

01:38.431 --> 01:39.265
(<i> belching</i> )

01:42.143 --> 01:44.771
(<i> grunting</i> )

01:44.854 --> 01:47.315
AHH! HMMMP!

02:29.691 --> 02:31.192
(<i> heart pounding</i> )

02:42.829 --> 02:46.165
(<i> sniffing</i> )

02:58.303 --> 02:59.345
(<i> sighing</i> )

03:14.360 --> 03:16.571
(<i> kissing sounds</i> )

03:56.486 --> 03:58.237
COME ON, SPUNKY.

03:58.321 --> 04:02.116
{\an1}LET'S GO BEFORE YOU GO
ON THE BED AGAIN.

04:02.200 --> 04:02.533
SPUNKY?

04:02.617 --> 04:05.328
{\an3}SPUNKY?

04:05.411 --> 04:08.122
MAYBE HE WAS THIRSTY.

04:08.206 --> 04:08.831
NO.

04:08.915 --> 04:11.668
MAYBE HE WAS HUNGRY.

04:13.628 --> 04:14.754
NO.

04:14.837 --> 04:17.464
WHERE COULD HE BE?

04:17.548 --> 04:18.757
(<i> whimpering</i> )

04:18.841 --> 04:22.095
(<i> whimpering</i> )

04:25.598 --> 04:28.393
(<i> whimpering</i> )

04:36.484 --> 04:39.070
ARE YOU DIZZY,
SPUNKY?

04:40.279 --> 04:42.198
WHAT WERE YOU DOING
IN THERE?

04:42.281 --> 04:43.616
NO. DON'T TELL ME.

04:43.700 --> 04:44.367
IT'S SICK. IT'S WRONG.

04:44.450 --> 04:47.120
DO YOU KNOW
WHAT I'VE MOPPED UP

04:47.203 --> 04:48.997
WITH THAT THING?

04:49.080 --> 04:50.581
(<i> whimpering</i> )

04:50.665 --> 04:51.416
BLAH, BLAH, BLAH, BLAH.

04:51.499 --> 04:55.294
YOU MAY NOT KNOW
WHAT'S GOOD FOR YOU

04:55.378 --> 04:56.462
BUT I DO.

04:56.546 --> 04:58.089
ONE DAY, YOU'LL THANK ME.

04:58.172 --> 05:02.051
NOW, GO ON AND PLAY.

05:05.972 --> 05:07.515
SPUNKY!

05:10.143 --> 05:11.310
THERE.

05:14.188 --> 05:15.565
AH! NO, YOU DON'T.

05:15.648 --> 05:18.359
SAY GOOD-BYE
TO YOUR GIRLFRIEND.

05:18.443 --> 05:20.903
SPUNKY, LET GO.

05:20.987 --> 05:24.532
I SAID LET GO!

05:27.827 --> 05:29.412
HMMPH.

05:29.495 --> 05:30.580
YIKES!

05:30.663 --> 05:31.497
{\an3}DROP IT!

05:39.714 --> 05:41.841
(<i> garbage disposal grinding</i> )

06:16.542 --> 06:18.920
THIS IS SERIOUS.

06:19.003 --> 06:21.881
(<i> people laughing</i> )

06:25.885 --> 06:27.387
Wake up! Wake up!

06:27.470 --> 06:29.472
Does your pet have a problem?

06:29.555 --> 06:32.433
{\an1}Does he experience
any of these problems:

06:32.517 --> 06:34.811
Violent mood swings?

06:34.894 --> 06:37.980
Overindulgence?

06:38.064 --> 06:38.981
Unhealthy attachments

06:39.065 --> 06:41.692
to inanimate objects?

06:41.776 --> 06:43.027
YEAH, YEAH.

06:43.111 --> 06:46.155
IF SO, THEN THE QUESTION IS

06:46.239 --> 06:48.991
WHEN ARE YOU GOING
TO DO SOMETHING ABOUT IT?

06:49.075 --> 06:51.160
REMEMBER DR. KATZ,
PET PSYCHOLOGIST EXTRAORDINAIRE.

06:51.244 --> 06:54.539
I'M SURROUNDED
BY BEAUTIFUL WOMEN.

06:54.622 --> 06:55.957
(<i> women giggling</i> )

07:12.098 --> 07:14.517
(<i> barking</i> )

07:17.937 --> 07:21.607
(<i> whimpering</i> )

07:25.611 --> 07:26.863
HELLO THERE.

07:26.946 --> 07:27.864
I'M DR. KATZ.

07:27.947 --> 07:30.575
(<i> snarling</i> )

07:30.658 --> 07:32.201
BACK!

07:32.285 --> 07:34.245
BACK, YOU MONSTER!

07:34.328 --> 07:35.538
I'LL BE RIGHT WITH YOU.

07:35.621 --> 07:41.419
I'M HAVING A LITTLE TROUBLE
WITH A PATIENT.

07:43.004 --> 07:44.505
(<i> snarling continues</i> )

07:47.341 --> 07:49.385
GOOD WORK TODAY, MR. BUNNY.

07:49.468 --> 07:50.761
I FEEL SO LIGHT.

07:50.845 --> 07:52.471
THANKS, DOC.

07:52.555 --> 07:55.892
NOW, WHAT SEEMS
TO BE THE PROBLEM?

07:55.975 --> 07:58.144
MY DOG SPUNKY

07:58.227 --> 08:00.938
IS IN LOVE
WITH THIS HERE MOP.

08:01.022 --> 08:02.315
HE'S BECOMING
TOO ATTACHED.

08:02.398 --> 08:05.610
HE NEVER LETS IT
OUT OF HIS SIGHT.

08:05.693 --> 08:07.904
LAST NIGHT, HE TRIED
TO ELOPE WITH IT.

08:09.238 --> 08:13.576
I'M AT THE END OF MY ROPE.

08:13.659 --> 08:14.076
I UNDERSTAND.

08:14.160 --> 08:16.120
I'VE SEEN WORSE.

08:16.204 --> 08:18.289
BUT YOU HAVE TO ADMIT

08:18.372 --> 08:20.249
IT'S A VERY...

08:20.333 --> 08:23.127
ATTRACTIVE MOP.

08:25.087 --> 08:26.255
VERY WELL.

08:26.339 --> 08:28.257
I'M SURE I CAN HELP YOU.

08:28.341 --> 08:30.718
LET'S GO INTO MY OFFICE.

08:44.148 --> 08:45.650
HUH?

08:58.579 --> 09:00.498
YOUR DOG APPEARS NORMAL.

09:00.581 --> 09:04.126
HOWEVER, I WOULD LIKE
TO HAVE A WORD ALONE.

09:04.210 --> 09:05.044
STAY HERE, SPUNKY.

09:05.127 --> 09:07.672
I'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

09:07.755 --> 09:08.130
{\an3}NO!

09:08.214 --> 09:11.550
WITH THE MOP.

09:15.263 --> 09:16.973
(<i> whimpering</i> )

09:17.056 --> 09:18.057
IT'S ALL RIGHT, SPUNKY.

09:18.140 --> 09:20.518
HE'LL BE RIGHT BACK.

09:20.601 --> 09:22.144
JUST AS I THOUGHT.

09:22.228 --> 09:24.397
YOUR DOG IS
PERFECTLY NORMAL

09:24.480 --> 09:29.318
{\an1}BUT WHAT WE HAVE HERE
IS A VERY SICK MOP.

09:29.402 --> 09:34.198
I MUST KEEP IT FOR OBSERVATION.

09:35.741 --> 09:36.784
(<i> whimpering</i> )

09:48.212 --> 09:50.506
I'M SORRY, SPUNKY.

09:50.589 --> 09:51.841
I'LL MAKE IT UP
TO YOU SOMEHOW.

09:51.924 --> 09:55.428
HMMPH.

09:56.178 --> 09:59.223
BUT, SPUNKY

09:59.307 --> 10:01.976
{\an1}I WAS JUST
TRYING TO HELP.

10:02.059 --> 10:03.352
WAIT, SPUNKY.

10:03.436 --> 10:04.937
{\an3}SPUNKY!

10:19.702 --> 10:22.288
WHAT THE..?

10:35.343 --> 10:36.969
ATTA BOY, SPUNKY.

10:43.184 --> 10:44.143
(<i> kissing sounds</i> )

10:44.226 --> 10:45.311
(<i> laughing</i> )

10:45.394 --> 10:48.522
(<i> kissing sounds</i> )

10:48.606 --> 10:51.609
(<i> fireworks exploding</i> )

11:13.547 --> 11:15.424
♪ MI-MI-MI-MI ♪

11:15.508 --> 11:18.427
♪ FIGARO, FIGARO, FIGARO ♪

11:18.511 --> 11:20.429
♪ LA-LA-LA-LA-LAAA ♪

11:20.513 --> 11:22.098
♪ LA-LA... ♪

11:22.181 --> 11:23.516
(<i> choking sounds</i> )

11:35.194 --> 11:35.694
AHHH!

11:43.327 --> 11:45.371
SPUNKY, PEW!

11:45.454 --> 11:48.791
{\an3}BAD DOG!

11:48.874 --> 11:50.000
COR!

11:50.084 --> 11:53.212
WHERE'S THAT HORRIFIC SMELL
COMING FROM?

12:03.305 --> 12:05.349
(<i> screams</i> )

12:05.433 --> 12:08.018
AH, YECH!

12:13.607 --> 12:14.984
LOOKS LIKE WE SHOULD

12:15.067 --> 12:17.319
SPEND THE DAY
AT THE LAUNDROMAT.

12:24.493 --> 12:25.786
SPUNKY!

12:41.844 --> 12:44.513
AH, WHAT A WRECK!

12:44.597 --> 12:48.184
WHEN WAS THE LAST TIME
WE DID LAUNDRY?

12:48.267 --> 12:49.560
DO YOU REMEMBER, SPUNKY?

12:50.769 --> 12:53.814
THIS PLACE LOOKS LIKE A PIGSTY.

12:53.898 --> 12:57.067
WHAT, YOU GOT A PROBLEM
WITH THAT?

12:57.151 --> 12:58.861
<i>AMSCRAY!</i>

12:58.944 --> 13:01.864
(<i> angry mumbling</i> )

13:01.947 --> 13:04.200
OY! EWW! THIS IS AWFUL.

13:04.283 --> 13:06.202
(<i> coughs</i> )

13:06.285 --> 13:08.454
TERRIBLE. ICK!

13:08.537 --> 13:13.709
HOW DID WE EVER LET IT
GET THIS BAD?

13:27.932 --> 13:29.475
Rocko:
SORRY, SPUNKY!

13:29.558 --> 13:31.227
LAST ONE.

13:31.310 --> 13:33.646
HMMM, BUT WHAT TO WEAR?

13:33.729 --> 13:35.564
THE ONLY THING CLEAN

13:35.648 --> 13:37.608
IS MY LUCKY SHIRT.

13:37.691 --> 13:38.984
(<i> growling</i> )

13:39.068 --> 13:42.988
NOW, NOW, IT IS, TOO,
A LUCKY SHIRT.

13:43.072 --> 13:45.908
<i>REMEMBER WHEN I WON</i>
<i>AT THE CARNIVAL</i>

13:45.991 --> 13:49.078
<i>AND WE FIRST SAW MELBA</i>

13:49.161 --> 13:50.037
<i>AND WHEN I FIRST GOT YOU?</i>

13:56.418 --> 13:59.630
{\an1}I KNOW, BUT IT'S
THE ONLY CLEAN ONE LEFT.

13:59.713 --> 14:01.131
I CAN'T GO NAKED.

14:32.871 --> 14:34.915
HOLD THESE WHILE I GET THE DOOR.

14:38.544 --> 14:41.046
(<i> mule-like braying</i> )

14:45.884 --> 14:50.639
{\an1}GOING TO NEED A BUNCH
OF CHANGE FOR THIS LOAD.

15:25.382 --> 15:27.301
WE NEED THIS BIG ONE.

15:36.268 --> 15:38.187
(<i> coughing and wheezing</i> )

15:58.916 --> 16:00.417
(<i> burping</i> )

16:03.921 --> 16:05.422
(<i> burping</i> )

16:09.635 --> 16:12.471
(<i> loud pounding</i> )

16:12.554 --> 16:15.933
HEY, IS THIS YOURS?

16:16.016 --> 16:17.184
(<i> timidly:</i> )
YES.

16:44.837 --> 16:48.590
BLIMEY, THESE PLACES ARE BORING.

16:52.344 --> 16:54.012
MY CLOTHES!

16:57.349 --> 17:00.102
OW, OW, OW, OW, OW, OW!

17:00.185 --> 17:02.312
(<i> car horn honking</i> )

17:17.327 --> 17:20.873
MAN, THAT'S GOT TO HURT.

17:26.962 --> 17:32.342
THERE! NO MORE
OF THIS HOPPING NOW.

17:34.094 --> 17:35.220
THAT'S ENOUGH.

17:40.350 --> 17:42.144
(<i> smashing sound</i> )

17:44.563 --> 17:47.441
LAUNDRY DAY
IS A VERY DANGEROUS DAY.

18:10.088 --> 18:12.007
OH!

18:13.884 --> 18:15.385
(<i> screaming</i> )

18:15.469 --> 18:16.929
MY CLOTHES ARE ON FIRE.

18:17.012 --> 18:18.096
(<i> Rocko screaming</i> )

18:19.973 --> 18:22.726
(<i> yelping</i> )

18:26.230 --> 18:28.357
AHHHHHH!

18:28.440 --> 18:31.193
SPUNKY, ARE YOU ALL RIGHT?

18:31.276 --> 18:34.112
EW, YOU'RE ALL WET!

18:34.196 --> 18:35.531
COME ON, SPUNKY.

18:35.614 --> 18:37.366
WE GOT TO DRY YOU OFF.

18:37.449 --> 18:39.618
I DON'T WANT YOU CATCHING COLD.

18:39.701 --> 18:41.328
I'LL PUT IT ON LOW.

18:43.205 --> 18:44.540
(<i> buzzer sounds</i> )

18:44.623 --> 18:45.541
THERE YOU GO, SPUNKY.

18:45.624 --> 18:47.334
GOOD AS NEW.

19:00.681 --> 19:01.890
{\an3}SPUNKY!

19:01.974 --> 19:04.184
STATIC CLING.

19:04.268 --> 19:06.061
CAN'T SEE.

19:06.144 --> 19:09.231
MUST... REMOVE... CUPS.

19:12.192 --> 19:15.320
HOW DARE YOU?!

19:20.325 --> 19:22.035
(<i> screams</i> )

19:23.996 --> 19:25.622
Rocko:
LOOK IT, SPUNKY.

19:25.706 --> 19:28.292
WE'RE ALL DONE
AND NOTHING'S MISSING.

19:28.375 --> 19:30.127
NOT A SINGLE SOCK GONE.

19:30.210 --> 19:32.212
THIS HAS NEVER HAPPENED BEFORE.

19:32.296 --> 19:33.630
THIS IS A LUCKY SHIRT.

19:33.714 --> 19:37.050
I SO HAPPY.

19:37.134 --> 19:39.011
MY SHIRT! HEY!

19:41.471 --> 19:43.223
GIVE ME BACK MY SHIRT.

19:45.017 --> 19:46.602
HELLO, ROCKO!

19:46.685 --> 19:47.853
(<i> evil laughing</i> )

19:47.936 --> 19:50.355
OH, NO, THE GRIPES.

19:50.439 --> 19:51.356
I'VE HEARD ABOUT THEM.

19:51.440 --> 19:55.652
THEY STEAL YOUR SOCKS
AND HURT YOUR CLOTHES.

19:58.697 --> 20:00.157
HA!

20:02.868 --> 20:05.120
ANOTHER JOB
WELL DONE.

20:05.203 --> 20:07.873
I'VE GOT TO GET ME SHIRT
OUT OF HERE.

20:19.343 --> 20:21.470
THERE'S ME LUCKY SHIRT.

20:29.353 --> 20:31.563
EAT STEEL, ROCKO!

20:45.953 --> 20:47.788
OOPS, WRONG DRYER.

20:47.871 --> 20:51.458
HOW DARE YOU?!

20:57.506 --> 20:58.799
UH...

20:58.882 --> 21:01.927
(<i> horn honking</i> )

21:08.308 --> 21:10.435
(<i> barking</i> )

21:10.519 --> 21:12.604
MELBA?

21:12.688 --> 21:15.190
I TOLD YOU THIS SHIRT WAS LUCKY.

21:15.273 --> 21:16.566
CLEAN AND PRESSED.

21:16.650 --> 21:18.610
I EVEN GOT MY DOLLAR BACK.

21:19.987 --> 21:22.990
WELL, SPUNKY, FEELS GOOD
TO GET THE LAUNDRY DONE.

21:23.073 --> 21:25.242
SURE LOOKS DIFFERENT,
ALL NEAT AND CLEAN.

21:25.325 --> 21:26.576
I HARDLY RECOGNIZE

21:26.660 --> 21:27.703
THIS PLACE WITHOUT
THE DIRTY LAUNDRY

21:27.786 --> 21:30.664
STREWN ABOUT.

21:30.747 --> 21:32.374
(<i> pounding noise</i> )

21:36.670 --> 21:38.839
{\an1}Man:
EXCUSE ME!

21:38.922 --> 21:41.591
HAVE YOU SEEN A WASHER
COME THIS WAY?

21:41.967 --> 21:43.552
THANK YOU.

21:52.352 --> 21:55.439
